OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FRichens, 35, was ordered to serve at
OL,7,Fleast 16 years and one month behind
OL,8,Fbars in February this year at Oxford
OL,9,FCrown Court after admitting Ms
OL,10,FVaughan's murder.
OL,12,FThe Solicitor General referred the
OL,13,Fsentence to the Court of Appeal, with
OL,14,Fbarristers telling a hearing on
OL,15,FThursday that it was "unduly lenient"
OL,16,Fas the sentencing judge failed to take
OL,17,Fsufficient account of aggravating
OL,18,Ffeatures in the case, and reduced the
OL,19,Fsentence too much to take account of
OL,20,FRichens' learning disabilities.
OL,26,@wD@VOUwD@eO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FBarristers for Richens, who attended
OL,7,Fthe hearing via a video link from HMP
OL,8,FWhitemoor in Cambridgeshire, said that
OL,9,Fthe sentence was not unduly lenient
OL,10,Fand should remain unchanged.
OL,12,FAt the end of the hearing in London,
OL,13,Fthree senior judges increased the
OL,14,Fminimum term to 19-and-a-half years.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FIn a ruling, Lord Justice Males,
OL,7,Fsitting with Mrs Justice Cutts and
OL,8,FJudge Sylvia de Bertodano, said that
OL,9,Fthe sentence could not be increased
OL,10,F"unless we were satisfied that the
OL,11,Fjudge reached a conclusion... that was
OL,12,Foutside the range that was reasonably
OL,13,Fopen to him".
OL,15,FBut he concluded: "We are so satisfied
OL,16,Fin this case.
OL,18,F"This was a particularly brutal
OL,19,Fmurder, with a host of aggravating
OL,20,Ffactors.
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@LO]wD@SOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,F"The judge said that Ms Vaughan was
OL,7,F"particularly vulnerable because of
OL,8,Fher various disabilities".
OL,10,FHe continued that evidence of Richens'
OL,11,Flearning disabilities "does not
OL,12,Fjustify any conclusion that these
OL,13,Fdifficulties lessened, materially or
OL,14,Findeed at all, the offender's
OL,15,Fculpability".
OL,17,FHe said: "The fact of learning
OL,18,Fdisabilities or other intellectual
OL,19,Fdifficulties does not necessarily mean
OL,20,Fthat an offender's culpability is
OL,21,Freduced.
OL,26,@nD@AO]oD@AOUpD@YO]sD@WOUwD@LO]yD@JOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,F"Many people with such problems manage
OL,7,Fto lead perfectly satisfactory and law-
OL,8,Fabiding lives."
OL,10,FLord Justice Males said that Richens
OL,11,Fand Ms Vaughan began a relationship in
OL,12,F2023, but that Richens was
OL,13,F"controlling and violent towards her"
OL,14,Fwith "multiple instances of such
OL,15,Fviolence", including punching,
OL,16,Fstrangling and striking.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@OO]uD@AOUuD@eO]vD@FOUwD@IO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FWhile Ms Vaughan tried to leave him on
OL,7,Fseveral occasions, "unfortunately she
OL,8,Falways went back, and the treatment of
OL,9,Fher continued", the judge said,
OL,10,Fadding: "It is a story that makes for
OL,11,Fmost unhappy reading."
OL,13,FHe continued that Richens and Ms
OL,14,FVaughan were seen together on the
OL,15,Fevening of May 29 last year, before
OL,16,FRichens launched a "brutal and
OL,17,Fsustained attack", including punching
OL,18,Fher, kicking her, and hitting her with
OL,19,Fan implement, causing a traumatic
OL,20,Fbrain injury and multiple bone
OL,21,Ffractures.
OL,26,@oD@TOUqD@NO]rD@IOUsD@VO]xD@TOUyD@QO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FAfter attempting to clean the
OL,7,Fproperty, Richens called the police
OL,8,Fthe next morning and said that he
OL,9,Fbelieved he had accidentally killed
OL,10,Fsomeone and that he had no memory of
OL,11,Fthe incident, but pleaded guilty to
OL,12,Fmurder in December.
OL,14,FIn written submissions on behalf of
OL,15,Fthe Solicitor General, Peter Ratliff
OL,16,Fsaid that in the days before the
OL,17,Fkilling, Ms Vaughan had sought refuge
OL,18,Fwith a friend, with whom Richens
OL,19,Fbelieved she had engaged in sexual
OL,20,Frelations.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784839668
OL,3,CMan has sentence increased for
OL,4,C'brutal' murder of former partner
OL,6,FHe continued that the "appropriate
OL,7,Fminimum term was significantly longer
OL,8,Fthan the 16 years and 1 month
OL,9,Fidentified".
OL,11,FIn court, Mr Ratliff said that Richens
OL,12,Fhad made a "concerted effort" to
OL,13,Fconceal his crime, and that the murder
OL,14,Finvolved "extreme violence".
OL,16,FAndrew Selby KC, for Richens, said the
OL,17,Freduction for his learning
OL,18,Fdisabilities was "modest" and
OL,19,F"calibrated", and that the sentencing
OL,20,Fjudge, Ian Pringle KC, "did not err in
OL,21,Fhis ultimate findings".
OL,26,@nD@WOUqD@KO]tD@LOUtD@]O]vD@JOUvD@[O]zD@
OL,26,AROUzD@YO]{D@AOU{D@LO]|D@XOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
